      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add cost summary display style",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAdds a configurable display style for the cost summary so users can choose how cost information appears in the status menu.\r\n\r\nUsers can now choose:\r\n\r\n- **Inline only**: shows the cost summary directly in the main menu.\r\n- **Submenu only**: shows the detailed Cost submenu instead.\r\n- **Both**: shows both the main menu summary and the detailed Cost submenu.\r\n\r\nThe default remains **Both** for existing enabled users, while first-time enablement persists the initial style so the setting does not change unexpectedly after relaunch.\r\n\r\n## What Changed\r\n\r\n- Added a `costSummaryDisplayStyle` preference with `Inline only`, `Submenu only`, and `Both`.\r\n- Updated status menu rendering so inline summaries and Cost submenus respect the selected style.\r\n- Fixed relaunch behavior so enabling cost summary does not silently switch display style on next app start.\r\n- Updated Preferences UI:\r\n  - Added separate helper text under **Display style** explaining where each option appears.\r\n  - Changed **History window** from a stepper/text field to a menu picker matching the rest of Preferences.\r\n  - Added helper text explaining that the history window controls how many days of local usage logs appear in the menu.\r\n  - Removed live provider cost-refresh diagnostics from the General pane to keep the setting focused on configuration.\r\n- Added the new preference copy across all localized string catalogs to avoid mixed-language Preferences UI.\r\n- Split existing oversized menu/test files slightly to keep `make check` passing after the branch updates.\r\n\r\n## Why\r\n\r\nPreviously, enabling cost summary could show both an inline summary and a Cost submenu at the same time, which made the menu feel redundant for users who only wanted one presentation style.\r\n\r\nThis change gives users explicit control over that behavior while making the Preferences UI explain the difference clearly:\r\n\r\n- “Inline” means the cost summary appears directly in the main menu.\r\n- “Submenu” means detailed cost history appears under the Cost submenu.\r\n\r\nThe Preferences cleanup also keeps runtime/debug cost-refresh state out of the General settings pane, where it was noisy and provider-specific.\r\n\r\n## Validation\r\n\r\n- `swift test --filter PreferencesPaneSmokeTests`\r\n- `swift test --filter LocalizationLanguageCatalogTests`\r\n- `swift test --filter StatusMenuPersistentRefreshTests`\r\n- `make check`\r\n- `git diff --check`\r\n\r\n## Screenshot\r\n### menu \r\nbefore:\r\n<img width=\"450\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-24 at 09 54 51\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7ee2f748-257a-4b0f-a67b-59bffb973ce6\" />\r\n\r\nafter:\r\n- when inline selected\r\n<img width=\"311\" height=\"300\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-24 at 09 54 16\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8682ab67-01ef-456e-8801-8fa6c45f22f0\" />\r\n\r\n- when submenu selected\r\n<img width=\"310\" height=\"146\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-24 at 09 54 32\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d1e8ac14-8f8e-4a3b-a426-467e59d25778\" />\r\n\r\n### cost setting \r\nbefore:\r\n<img width=\"550\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-27 at 13 27 52\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d83daddc-a77a-49e3-b6d4-52ea4d4dec23\" />\r\n\r\nafter:\r\n<img width=\"550\" alt=\"Screenshot 2026-06-27 at 13 43 34\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/710e8d2b-4443-46ba-abfd-36ddf04289af\" />",
